Restructured text allows to define special paragraphs like notes, warnings, etc. that will stand out from the surrounding text. They call these [admonitions|http://docutils.sourceforge.net/docs/ref/rst/directives.html#admonitions]. For example:

{code}
.. note:: This paragraph should stand out from the surrounding text.

.. warning:: This paragraph should stand out too.
{code}

Currently, the generated HTML does surround the note in a {{<div>}} with the appropriate class, but it shows up as normal text.

400 error responses are currently returned as difficult-to-parse HTML:

